---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Base title="Terms of Service — Code Cowboys LLC" description="Terms of Service for Code Cowboys LLC apps and website.">
  <Nav />

  <div class="terms-wrap">
    <div class="inner terms-inner">

      <div class="terms-header">
        <div class="section-label">Legal</div>
        <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
        <div class="meta">
          <span>Effective Date: May 16, 2026</span>
          <span>Last Updated: May 16, 2026</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="terms-body">

        <div class="summary-box">
          <h2>Important Disclaimer — Not Medical Advice</h2>
          <p>Our health-related applications are tracking tools, not medical advice. The application is not a substitute for professional medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment. Always consult a qualified healthcare provider regarding any medical condition, dietary decision, or treatment plan.</p>
        </div>

        <h2>1. About Code Cowboys</h2>
        <p>Code Cowboys LLC is a Michigan-based software development studio. We publish mobile and web applications, including health and wellness tracking tools and field journaling applications.</p>

        <h2>2. Important Disclaimer — Not Medical Advice</h2>
        <p>Our health-related applications are tracking tools, not medical advice. Any related products are intended to help you log and visualize your own data. The information displayed by our applications, including reference values for nutrients, minerals, or other tracked elements, is provided for general informational purposes only.</p>
        <div class="callout">The application is not a substitute for professional medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment. Always consult a qualified healthcare provider regarding any medical condition, dietary decision, or treatment plan. Never disregard professional medical advice or delay seeking it because of something you read or saw in our applications.</div>
        <p>We do not warrant the accuracy, completeness, or suitability of any reference data for any specific medical purpose. Decisions about your health are your responsibility and should be made in consultation with appropriate medical professionals.</p>

        <h2>3. Account Registration</h2>
        <p>To use certain features, you must create an account. You agree to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Provide accurate, current information</li>
          <li>Keep your password secure</li>
          <li>Notify us promptly of any unauthorized access</li>
          <li>Be responsible for activity under your account</li>
        </ul>
        <p>You must be at least 13 years old to create an account. If you are under the age of majority in your jurisdiction, you must have permission from a parent or guardian to use our services.</p>

        <h2>4. Subscriptions and Payments</h2>
        <p>Some features require a paid subscription. Subscription terms:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Subscriptions are processed through Apple, Google, or Stripe depending on the platform</li>
          <li>Subscription pricing is shown before purchase</li>
          <li>Subscriptions auto-renew unless canceled before the renewal date</li>
          <li>Cancellation is managed through the platform where you subscribed (App Store, Google Play, or our web portal)</li>
          <li>Refunds are handled according to the policies of the platform where you purchased</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>5. Acceptable Use</h2>
        <p>You agree not to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Use our applications for any unlawful purpose</li>
          <li>Attempt to reverse engineer, decompile, or extract source code from our applications</li>
          <li>Use our services to harass, harm, or deceive others</li>
          <li>Attempt to gain unauthorized access to our systems</li>
          <li>Resell or redistribute our applications or any data they generate</li>
        </ul>
        <p>We reserve the right to suspend or terminate accounts that violate these Terms.</p>

        <h2>6. Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p>Code Cowboys LLC owns all rights to our applications, including the software, visual design, and content we create. You retain ownership of the data you enter into our applications. We do not claim ownership of your health tracking data or other personal logs.</p>
        <p>Reference data displayed in our applications may be sourced from third parties with appropriate attribution. Our use of such data does not transfer any rights to the underlying data sources.</p>

        <h2>7. Privacy</h2>
        <p>Your use of our applications is also governed by our <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.</p>

        <h2>8. Disclaimers and Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>Our applications are provided "as is" without warranties of any kind, express or implied. We do not warrant that:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>The applications will be uninterrupted or error-free</li>
          <li>Defects will be corrected immediately</li>
          <li>The information provided is accurate, complete, or reliable for any specific purpose</li>
        </ul>
        <p>To the maximum extent permitted by law, Code Cowboys LLC and its principals are not liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages arising from your use of our applications, including but not limited to damages for personal injury, lost data, or medical decisions made in reliance on application data.</p>
        <p>You acknowledge that you use our applications at your own risk and that you are responsible for any decisions, including health and dietary decisions, that you make based on data displayed by our applications.</p>

        <h2>9. Indemnification</h2>
        <p>You agree to defend, indemnify, and hold harmless Code Cowboys LLC from any claims arising from your violation of these Terms, your use of our applications, or your violation of any third-party rights.</p>

        <h2>10. Termination</h2>
        <p>We may suspend or terminate your access to our applications at any time if you violate these Terms. You may terminate your account at any time by contacting us or using in-app account deletion features. Upon termination, the rights and licenses granted to you will end.</p>

        <h2>11. Governing Law</h2>
        <p>These Terms are governed by the laws of the State of Michigan, without regard to its conflict-of-law provisions. Any disputes arising from these Terms or your use of our applications will be resolved in the state or federal courts located in Michigan.</p>

        <h2>12. Changes to These Terms</h2>
        <p>We may update these Terms occasionally. When we make significant changes, we will update the "Last Updated" date and notify users via email or in-app notification. Continued use of our applications after a change indicates acceptance of the updated Terms.</p>

        <h2>13. Contact</h2>
        <div class="contact-block">
          <p><strong>Code Cowboys LLC</strong></p>
          <p>Email: <a href="mailto:legal@code-cowboys.com">legal@code-cowboys.com</a></p>
          <p>Website: <a href="https://code-cowboys.com">code-cowboys.com</a></p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <Footer />
</Base>

<style>
  .terms-wrap {
    padding: 60px 0 80px;
  }

  .terms-inner {
    max-width: 760px;
  }

  .terms-header {
    margin-bottom: 50px;
    padding-bottom: 32px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .terms-header h1 {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: 48px;
    font-weight: 900;
    color: #f5ead6;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    line-height: 1.05;
  }

  .meta {
    display: flex;
    gap: 24px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .meta span {
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--text-faint);
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  .terms-body h2 {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: 24px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #f5ead6;
    margin: 44px 0 14px;
    padding-top: 44px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .terms-body h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; padding-top: 0; border-top: none; }

  .terms-body p {
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 14px;
    font-weight: 300;
  }

  .terms-body ul {
    margin: 0 0 16px 0;
    padding-left: 20px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 6px;
  }

  .terms-body li {
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    line-height: 1.7;
    font-weight: 300;
  }

  .terms-body li::marker { color: var(--gold); }

  .terms-body a {
    color: var(--gold);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }

  .terms-body strong { color: var(--text-muted); font-weight: 500; }

  .summary-box {
    background: var(--bg2);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--gold);
    padding: 24px 28px;
    margin-bottom: 44px;
    border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0;
  }

  .summary-box h2 {
    margin: 0 0 12px !important;
    padding: 0 !important;
    border: none !important;
    font-size: 18px !important;
  }

  .summary-box p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .callout {
    background: rgba(201,144,30,0.06);
    border: 1px solid rgba(201,144,30,0.2);
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 14px 18px;
    font-size: 13px;
    color: #8a7254;
    margin: 4px 0 20px;
    font-style: italic;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .contact-block {
    background: var(--bg2);
    padding: 24px 28px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 6px;
  }

  .contact-block p { margin: 0; }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .terms-header h1 { font-size: 36px; }
    .terms-wrap { padding: 40px 0 60px; }
  }
</style>